N E X T 1 2 H O U R S

𝐒𝟑𝐄𝟐 An ease in Gotham’s wintry grip affords Rachelle Harris an opportunity to pedal her way to her call time across town. After sipping a cold brew in the East Village she undocks an electric Citi Bike and heads west! Weaving her way through traffic she makes it to the Meatpacking District for a pair of afternoon shows for Peter Do. The occasion is Rachelle’s first walking for the acclaimed designer, which she takes with aplomb.

Pictured @rachellehrs in New York City. Film @damienneva at Next Management.

𝐒𝟑𝐄𝟏 Following an unforced two year hiatus, NEXT 12 Hours returns for a smashing runway debut of French beauty Marie Teissonnière. The season gets off to an auspicious start for Marie as she shoots a lookbook for @yellowlabelco in a 63rd story downtown penthouse. More than 10 looks later Marie makes her way across Lower Manhattan to One World Observatory where she reaches ever new heights on the 102nd floor walking for @christiancowan. At no point does Marie succumb to the dizzying heights, on the contrary, she scales them evermore!

A V A H A R I R I • K I A

“𝙸’𝚖 𝚍𝚘𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚜 𝚋𝚎𝚌𝚊𝚞𝚜𝚎 𝙸 𝚠𝚊𝚗𝚝 𝚝𝚘 𝚌𝚛𝚎𝚊𝚝𝚎 𝚜𝚘𝚖𝚎𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚋𝚎𝚊𝚞𝚝𝚒𝚏𝚞𝚕, 𝙸 𝚠𝚊𝚗𝚝 𝚝𝚘 𝚌𝚛𝚎𝚊𝚝𝚎 𝚊𝚛𝚝.”

Safe to say possessing an unimpeachable thesis, let alone wielding one, is fairly atypical for a model. Models model after all, their truths are self evident. For Ava Hariri-Kia, once upon a time the very idea of modeling was fanciful, a rarefied pursuit unattainable to but a select few and certainly not to a young woman who wears a size 14 dress. Accepting high fashion as it was was never on the cards for Ava, she sees things differently. Her every move in high fashion calls bullshit on the very foundations on which this industry is premised. Hers is not a rhetorical battle, it’s aesthetic, and one she’s quietly winning.

In 2020 Ava inked her first modeling contract with Next Management in the midst of lockdown, not long after having landed a page in that year’s September issue of Vogue with a portrait by Ethan James Green. She’s the daughter of Iranian emigrants, a native New Yorker, and fiercely Persian. Although advocacy comes naturally, embodiment is her preferred register, and these days her modeling couldn’t be more resonant than it is.

To understand how Ava got her start, one must meet her family, which is precisely where this film begins. One beautiful autumn Sunday we caught up with Ava, her mother Gisue, father Bahman, and sister Iman at Persian restaurant Persepolis on Manhattan’s Upper East Side. Over chaii چایی , a picture of Ava in emerges in its full, life-affirming brilliance. Raises those glasses high, this is Ava Hariri-Kia.

Pictured Ava Hariri-Kia @lava_ava @gisue.hariri @imanharirikia and Bahman Kia. Film @damienneva at Next Management.

#AvaHaririKia #NextModels #BodyInclusive #🇮🇷

¡Volumen arriba!

Black History Month has concluded, but the celebration of cultural diversity continues. Throughout February talent at Next Management also recorded themselves reading poetry en español.

This initiative was undertaken in support of Lesson Check-In, a nonprofit organization created by young, Black professionals, who strive to uplift students and give back to the communities that raised them.

By recording these literary texts, participating students are afforded a chance to experience a whole new world of literature.

Readings by @hiandramartinez @ambar_cristalz @luisana_gonzalez24 @yoelfernandez19 and @lineisymontero for @lessoncheckin.

This is the third and final volume of three films in a limited series paying tribute the cultural richness of diversity and inclusion.

#NextModels #LessonCheckin @wearegoodera #Goodera
